So take what the date is 2021-11-04 and convert it to it's unix timestamp representation (caveat: if this is just a date property you'll need to set the timestamp to midnight):

```const dateExample = '2021-11-04';
const dateObject = new Date(...dateExample.split("-"), 0, 0, 0, 0);
console.log(dateObject.getTime()) // Send this to HubSpot```
